text: The Apple M1 is an octa-core system on a chip that runs at 3.2 GHz. It is the first personal computer chip to have a 5-nm (0.00000019-in) process.https://www.apple.com/uk/mac/m1/, Apple M1 Chip The M1 runs Apple's own macOS and iPadOS operating systems. Initial support for the M1 SoC in the Linux kernel was released on June 27, 2021, with version 5.13. == References == Category:64-bit Apple silicon Category:Processors released in 2020s Category:Multi-core processors
title: Apple M1
